Introduction

WHIB is a South Korean eight-member boy group under C-JeS Entertainment. They made their official debut on November 8, 2023, with the single album "Cut-Out."

Combining the terms "WHITE" and "BLACK," WHIB conveys the confidence to display a range of charms, just as white and black are at opposing extremes of the color spectrum. At the same time, WHIB's desire to distinguish themselves from the many hues that exist between white and black may also be seen through endless encounters and events in the future.

WHIB has released their official fanclub name "AnD". It has a dual meaning, with the first one being (A)ll fans are WHIB's (n)umber one (D)ream and the second one being connecting white WHIB and black WHIB to into one WHIB!
